          • WHY GALAXY WATCH8 CLASSIC: Timeless design.* New lug system for easy band detachment & replacement.* Advanced health & sleep tracking features for total body wellness.* Improved user interface.* Personal AI assistant for hands free help.* 2-Yr Warranty
          • BUILT TO PERFORM. DESIGNED TO IMPRESS: Show off your style with an iconic design that blends tradition with cutting-edge innovation. A brighter screen makes everything easy to see, and a rotating bezel gives you access to your favorite apps
          • YOUR EVERY COMMAND, RIGHT ON YOUR WRIST: Get a little extra help with day-to-day tasks. Galaxy Watch 8 Classic features a personal AI assistant that helps you get things done hands-free. Simply speak the command and your Watch makes it happen
          • UNLOCK THE SECRETS TO BETTER SLEEP: When you get good sleep, it feels like anything is possible. Start each day with more energy and better focus using Advanced Sleep Coaching - improved with even more ways to help you sleep smarter
          • QUICK UPDATES, AT A GLANCE: Get updates, select apps and more with Now Bar, and an improved user experience. Now Bar conveniently puts the info you use the most - like weather, news and more - right on your main Watch screen
          • YOUR RUNNING GOALS, AT YOUR PACE: From a mile to a marathon, unleash the winning runner within using Running Coach. Your Watch analyzes factors such as your age, weight, oxygen levels and heart rate to guide you through your run
          • POWER FOR FAST-PACED LIFESTYLES: Your active lifestyle needs a watch that can keep up with you. Stay powered up and in charge with a battery thats built for even your busiest days.
          • BEAT BY BEAT, STAY ON TRACK: Gain deeper insight into your health with a watch that measures your vascular load. Galaxy Watch 8 Classic analyzes sleep, diet, activity and stress levels to keep you informed on the health of your heart and blood system
          • YOUR DAILY WELLNESS SNAPSHOT: Stay in the know about your wellness using Energy Score with Galaxy AI. Its a score based off yesterdays sleep, activity and heart rate, all collected by your Galaxy Watch 8 Classic

An ECOLOGO certification indicates that a product has met environmental performance standards, which include criteria in some or all of the following categories: materials, energy, manufacturing and operations, health and environment, product performance and use, and product stewardship and innovation. Products are evaluated on the applicable criteria through testing and auditing.

          How customer reviews and ratings work

          Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

          To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

            5.0 out of 5 stars This watch is a winner for sure.
            Reviewed in the United States on July 30, 2025
            Color: GraphiteSize: 40mmStyle: BluetoothPattern Name: Watch8Verified Purchase
            This watch has a lot of new stuff!

            A new bezel and a new way to attach the two bands. A lot more choices for watchfaces, and, many more color choices for background and font.

            There's a new way of using "tiles" ... instead of having one group of tiles and apps, now we have what you might call folders, with subfolders.

            You can see each "subfolder's" info at a glance when you're looking at that folder. From what I've seen so far, there are 3 "folders"... which are entitled Health; Fitness; Basic. You can add more "folders" and change its name too. Very versatile.

            You can put any tile or app in any of these areas of course. I put all the apps I had put on my Watch 7 into this watch's first "folder." I filed up the rest of the "folders" with anything else I needed.

            The bezel's new look is a little odd (a rounded square surrounds the round watchface). But, it's actually growing on me.

            There's a new way of putting on the bands, which is even different from the Watch 7. It's a little awkward trying to press the little bar while also getting the latch part to go in, but I succeeded.

            The new bands make the watch stand up from laying flat. No biggie, but it did make me wonder if the watch could still sit on its little disc charging thing (it did).

            When charging it, the watch face has more charging info on it.

            The new band is the same size as the previous version, but, I need to fasten it two holes closer to the end.

            As for battery, I've used the watch nearly all day. It's at 90%.

            I give this watch a 10 for sure. I like the look, feel, and all the new features of the Watch 8. Good job!!
